Git is developed by Linus Trovalds
Its a free and an open source version control system
It's a distributed/decentralize  version control system

Go to github.com
Open an account username and password
Create a Repository, name it eg-Git-tutorial
Copy the link Address

Go to your machine 
yum install git 
OR you can dowanload the and compile from the source 
#wget http://kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/git-1.8.4.tar.bz2
unzip the tar file
cd to git
./configure
make 
make install
check the installed version #git --version

setup username and email address
git config -global user.name yourname
git config -global user.email youremail@mailsite.com
This will be saved in user's homedirectory on .gitconfig file
Make a directory for testing git "eg-testgit", and Initialise it with git
#git init
##IT WILL CREATE A LOCAL GIT REPOSITORY ON YOUR CURRENT DIRECTORY##

Now link the local Repository with your remote github.com/username/Git-tutorial
#git remote add origin https://github.com/username/Git-tutorial.git

create a testgit.doc
once you have create a file, add it to local git repository
#git add testgit.doc
check the status with #git status
commit it to the repository
#git commit -m "add the description" 
To upload or add it to remote repository
#git push origin master
Enter "username" and "password"

Verification:- Go to github.com/username/Git-tutorial


